# Cache headers for Catalyst Slate (P3-07 from 2026-05-15 QA audit).
# Vite-fingerprinted asset paths are immutable and safe to cache for a
# year. HTML files must stay no-cache so users always pick up the
# latest deployed entry point.
#
# Slate may or may not honor this file — if it doesn't, the same
# headers can be configured in the Catalyst Console under
# Slate → Routes. See qa-audit-2026-05-15/FOLLOWUPS.md.

/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/*.html
  Cache-Control: no-cache
